OL,7,F"It was as though our grief was
OL,8,Ftreated as a threat, and our home as a
OL,9,Fsite of suspicion, something I will
OL,10,Fnever accept or forgive."
OL,12,FThe information gathered included that
OL,13,Fthe Lawrences' marriage had broken
OL,14,Fdown during the public inquiry into
OL,15,Ftheir son's death, and later in 2000
OL,16,Finformation linked to their civil
OL,17,Fclaim against the Metropolitan Police,
OL,18,Fincluding the claimed settlement
OL,19,Ffigure.
