OL,7,F"If the police, including the
OL,8,Fundercover police, had effectively
OL,9,Fpoliced the far-right and racist
OL,10,Fcriminal groups, instead of
OL,11,Fpersecuting and criminalising the
OL,12,Fvictims of racist violence, then
OL,13,Fperhaps some of the racist attacks,
OL,14,Fincluding some of the racist murders,
OL,15,Fthat plagued our communities during
OL,16,Fthe 1980s and 1990s, could have been
OL,17,Fprevented."
